name: flask-httpauth
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Flask-HTTPAuth" %}
{% set version = "4.7.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "f7199e7bad20d5b68b3f0b62bddfca7637c55087e9d02f605ae26e0de479fd94" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    - flask

test:
  imports:
    - flask_httpauth

about:
  home: http://github.com/miguelgrinberg/flask-httpauth/
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Basic and Digest HTTP authentication for Flask routes
  dev_url: http://github.com/miguelgrinberg/flask-httpauth/
  doc_url: http://flask-httpauth.readthedocs.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - synapticarbors
